tip.text: New hot dog place! Try the Chili cheese hot dog. Just wow. 50% opening offer in May 2017
Sehr individuelle und persönliche Beratung mit Getränk und viel Zeit. Plus super Kulanz bei Unzufriedenheit, mir wurden Gläser kostenlos nochmal angepasst. Sehr zu empfehlen!
Yummy "milled" ice cream made of sorbets and cream. Fair for 3€. Enjoy in the sun 😎
I don't understand the rating. When you leave this place you smell like you fried by yourself. And this chicken wings and cucumber portion (with loads of onions and wasabi sauce) is overpriced (18€)
Cool atmosphere and view over the city. The wealthy people of Zürich meet here, so expect that for your wallet 😊 Food and wine selection is outstanding good
When you're used to fancy international burgers, those won't attract you, but your wallet. Usual Swiss/Zermatt prices (25CHF). But the homemade fries are really good. Probably the best burger around😏
Try their smoothies between your dives and relax 😎

Come on a sunny day and walk the Smuts Track (no climbing but intermediate hiking). Last part dangerous if cloudy or windy. But the view is worth the walk up. Calculate 4-4,5 hours from KirstenboschBG
Probably one of the best restaurants around and for European tourists impressively cheap. They also gave a cool local wine list

formattedAddress: The Foundry, Prestwich St (at Cardiff St)

tip.text: Cool breakfast which comes nicely decorated for a good price
One of the most impressive places I have been to. Come on a sunny day and enjoy the sea and the picturesque breakwater and waves
Nice internationally influenced restaurant with an impressive selection of local wines. Good choice for your dinner
They are advertising with the tram but actually you'll be on a bus the whole day except for two stops. Nice wine tour programme and probably the best choice to get around in one day without car
Very good selection of wines and different tastings. They road to the main building is pretty impressive as well
Fantastic scenery and view. I personally found the wines okay but not outstanding. They have only red wines except for one Chardonnay
Cheap wine tastings when you come by wine tram tour and good lunch options
Great service and good selection of wines when you use the Wine Tram tour
Try the "Tiger of Bengal" when you like Gin. Very refreshing new drink
Changing craft beers every week with some very special and interesting unique brews. If you prefer a classic, go for the Stralauer Blond
Very good Italien food but pricey. Good selection of wine and friendly staff. Try the Burrata!
Smoky Rock'n'Roll bar with cheap beer and billiard (billard) table and dart. Better don't wear football shirts when it's not Bayern München :)
Unfortunately they don't serve the original pork-filled dumpling here but still great restaurant and full authentic Din Tai Fung experience. Try the truffle dumplings, you'll love it

formattedAddress: Mall of the Emirates (Sheikh Zayed Rd)

tip.text: Tourist restaurant with tourist prices. In the evening you must have dinner. Not only drinks here
Expensive drinks even for Dubai prices but great city view. You may have to wait for a table without reservation. Dress code: closed shoes and no shorts
Great hotel lobby and very nice rooms. Staff is helpful in general but the overall service lacks in quality. Breakfast is great
Try the Weasel Coffee (Huyen Thoai). Vietnamese specialty and worth a try with bitter notes of chocolate.
Most frightening place in PP. Plan a day and also visit the Genocide Museum. The audio tour is good to get an impression what happened here. Plan 2-3 hours. Sit down and listen
Must visit for your stay but bring good nerves. What you will see is hard. Plan a day and also visit the killing fields

Definitely a culinary experience but be careful with meat and fish, many stalls have everything uncooled boiling in the sun for hours.Might turn around your stomach and destroy the holidays experience

venue.name: ផ្សារ​ទួល​ទំពូង​ | Russian Market

tip.text: NO! ONE! HERE! Probably the most beautiful and lonely beach on the island (Nov '15)! Get a scooter and spend your day here off the Chinese crowds.
Enjoy the view and have a drink. The food is ok but not creative our outstanding. Bit expensive but ok. Probably the coolest place in PP with that view
Great place to hang around, work, meet friends or just enjoy HCMC. Good food quality. More expensive than city average but worth it. Try the Ham & Cheese sandwich and the Vietnamese milk-coffee

formattedAddress: 70B Lê Lợi St., District 1 (Nguyen Trung Truc)

tip.text: Cool to walk around, food is good, fresh and very cheap. Everything else around requires hard negotiation skills as everyone tries to squeeze every Dollar/Dong out of you. Buy not for more than 50%
Great place to deep-dive into Vietnamese markets. Bring your negotiation skills, tea and coffee are offered for 3-4 times more than worth it. The ladies are hard to crack but do love bargaining 👌🏻
Must have been impressive in the past, but with streets and cars less goods are traded on the water. Still cool to see but I expected more boats and items and a bigger market in general.

venue.name: Chợ Nổi Cái Răng (Cai Rang Floating Market)

tip.text: The Phô is really good but also the spring rolls. Easy to have dinner for two for less than 200K. No need to try the Cantella juice :)
Nice relaxation and usual Starbucks experience with prices that are 2-3 times higher than around. All Vietnamese coffee shops around are cheaper

formattedAddress: 210 Le Thanh Ton St., Dist. 1 (Pasteur St.)

tip.text: Pizza is good but both mozzarella and salami can't compete with the originals. However, due to low ceilings and tile floors, the place is very loud when full. Don't go here when you want to talk 🤐

venue.name: The Pizza Company Nguyen Thai Hoc

tip.text: Fantastic restaurant in the most touristic and pricy area of HCMC. But here you can easily have dinner and drinks for two for around 250K. Great restaurant! 👌🏻

location.address: 143 Bùi Viện, P .Phạm Ngũ Lão, Q.1
formattedAddress: 143 Bùi Viện, P .Phạm Ngũ Lão, Q.1

tip.text: Tourist warning: stunning view but all cocktails cost 345K VND and are not that well made and come with too much ice. Not worth the money and too noisy to have a chat with friends.
Cheap place to have a few beer on the busy Bui Vien for only 20-25k. But be warned, the servers are rude when you order less drinks than having people on the table. Mini chairs are uncomfortable ☺️
Wait on the tower and you may see crocodiles swimming around the lake. But the photos with baby crocodiles etc. must be made for advertising only. 10km walk is ok but prepare for high humidity.

Go for the Rambo Nemo Prawns. It will be the best decision while you're on Phu Quoc! Come around 8, when you're ready around 9ish the cook comes out and you can have a chat. Super fun and friendly guy
Great value for money! WiFi in the rooms a mess, sit down at the reception. Included breakfast is good, dinner pricy and not good. Go around the corner to Nemo for dinner. Good hotel to spend a week.
The Phó is great and much cheaper to more touristy places of Vietnam. Try also the colourful creative interpretations of the spring rolls
Gute Weinauswahl, Beratung und Preise! Nette Atmosphäre und man kann alles probieren :-)
Cool show and very entertaining. The champaign package is a good idea but the champaign is not the best for the price of 20€ each.
Book the Eiffel Tower View and ask for room 903. Best view over Paris for good value. The beds are short and breakfast is ok but not worth 9,50€ on top. Free WiFi. Good hotel for fair price
Great place for special occasions but also very pricy. The food is amazing, the service very friendly and professional and the wine recommendation fantastic. Plan +200€ as couple with menu and wine.
The Pelmeni are good but better at Matreshka down the road. The Russian Burger is nice and also the Stroganoff :-)
Love the breakfast #Honor6Plus
The ricotta pancakes (only for breakfast on weekends) will be your best decision on this very day ;)
Unbedingt den Lox probieren - mit Lachs, Salat und Frischkäse!
Great roof top bar with a view
Good location, okay drinks, fair prices as they come with a free buffet in the evenings. You can sit everywhere outside with your drinks :)
Amazing view over Lucca. How hot it might be, the view is worth the ascent and steps.
Picturesque setting to have breakfast, when you're guest of the hotel. The selection is continental and very good.
Amazing food concept and selection of Italian kitchen. Get your wine recommendation at the Chianti counter
The Gnocchi with Gorgonzola-Tartufo sauce will be the best decision in your life for a long time :)
Outstanding food quality and selection of mozzarellas. A mini mozzarella with pesto comes for everyone with every order. Great place!
The food is okay but the servers are kind of sales guys and try to approach you with starters, drinks, dessert and other stuff in a weird way, all the time. Very touristic place at all.
The Tagliatelle al-ragu are good but not outstanding. However, nice atmosphere and good prices, but we had 3 different servers and none of them spoke English. Prepare your tourist guide Italian! ;-)
Great place to spend your holidays in Tuscany for a fair price compared to the quality provided. But without a car you are fucked there. However, nearby Scansamo is worth a visit.
Great experience but don't go up if you are claustrophobic. The staircase is so small and tight, it may scare the shit out of you. Both ways take around 5 minutes, 12 rounds around the inner tower.
Great food quality, wines and services. But the small portion sizes are made to that you have to take both 1st and 2nd course to be filled up which makes the restaurant more expensive than it appear.
The Gnocchi (secret sauce) and Pici are very delicious. Try them. The house wine is great for only 3€ for 1/2 litre. Great quality far away from the busy tourist area
The Tagliolini with Red King Prawns are legendary. Nice restaurant, high food quality and fair prices. Go there if you are around and sick of overpriced tourist restaurants at the Spanish Steps
The Melanzane is just wow.
Fantastic gourmet store with tasty espresso for only 0,90€. Tourists: pay first at the entry :)
The Saltimbocca is fantastic, the Tiramisu, indeed, good but overrated. However, foursquare recommended the restaurant and it was a good decision going there. Good food and wine with a view
Best coffee around
Hotel fernab moderner Standards aber ok für eine Nacht ;-)
